      "helpText": "Indicates that the Category Stock Number in question is subject to special reporting requirements.  This data element was explicitly added to DHCP in the summer of 1991.  '0' indicates COMPUTERS (ADP/WP); '1' indicates CCTV (CLOSED CIRCUIT TV); '2' indicates AUDIOVISUAL (OTHER THAN CCTV); and '3' indicates PRINTING AND REPRODUCTION. Numbers '4' thru '9' are reserved.   '1' indicates CCTV (CLOSED CIRCUIT TV)   '2' indicates AUDIOVISUAL (OTHER THAN CCTV)   '3' indicates PRINTING & REPRODUCTION. ",
